doc.ContractDescription: SATURN'S DIVERSE RING SYSTEM PROVIDES AN IDEAL LABORATORY IN WHICH TO STUDY A VARIETY OF DYNAMICAL PROCESSES, SUCH AS DISK-SATELLITE INTERACTIONS, DENSITY AND BENDING WAVES, THE SHAPE AND STRUCTURE OF PRECESSING NARROW RINGLETS AND RING EDGES, AND SATELLITE WAKES. CASSINI STELLAR AND RADIO OCCULTATION DATA PROVIDE HIGH RESOLUTION SCANS OF RING STRUCTURE, AND BY COMBINING MULTIPLE CUTS ACROSS THE RINGS, THE GEOMETRY OF THE RING SYSTEM CAN BE RECONSTRUCTED TO SUB-KM PRECISION. WE WILL MEASURE THE LOCATIONS OF A STANDARD SET OF IDENTIFIABLE RING EDGES, RINGLETS, GAP EDGES, AND DENSITY WAVES IN THE RADIO SCIENCE (RSS) AND STELLAR (UVIS AND VIMS) OCCULTATION PROFILES, COMBINED WITH VOYAGER 1 AND 2 AND EARTH-BASED OCCULTATION DATA. USING THESE OCCULTATION TIMES, WE WILL DETERMINE SATURN'S POLE DIRECTION AND PRECESSION RATE, AND THE ABSOLUTE RADIUS SCALE OF SATURN'S RINGS TO SUB-KM ACCURACY. A KEY LIMITATION ON THE ACCURACY OF THE GEOMETRY IS THE UNCERTAINTY OF THE TRAJECTORY OF THE CASSINI SPACECRAFT DURING EACH OCCULTATION, WHICH CAN RESULT IN ERRORS IN THE RADIUS SCALE OF TENS OF KM. LEFT UNCORRECTED, THESE SYSTEMATIC ERRORS MASK MANY OF THE WEAKLY NON-CIRCULAR FEATURES IN THE RINGS, AND MAKE IT IMPOSSIBLE TO COMPARE DENSITY WAVES WITH MODEL PREDICTIONS IN ABSOLUTE RADIUS. WE WILL SOLVE FOR CORRECTIONS TO SPACECRAFT TRAJECTORIES DURING EACH OCCULTATION, USING DYNAMICALLY ACCURATE NUMERICAL INTEGRATIONS. FROM THE JOINT FITS, WE WILL DETERMINE THE ORBITAL ELEMENTS OF LOW WAVENUMBER NON-CIRCULAR FEATURE, INCLUDING THEIR APSIDAL PRECESSION RATES, WHICH WILL PROVIDE USEFUL CONSTRAINTS ON THE LOW-ORDER HARMONICS OF SATURN'S GRAVITATIONAL FIELD. WE WILL ALSO IDENTIFY AND MEASURE RING FEATURES WHOSE PRECESSION IS FORCED BY SATURN'S MOONS. THE ACCURATE KINEMATICAL AND GEOMETRICAL MODEL OF SATURN'S RINGS RESULTING FROM THIS WORK WILL PROVIDE THE GEOMETRICAL REFERENCE FRAME ESSENTIAL FOR MORE DETAILED DYNAMICAL INVESTIGATIONS OF THE ABUNDANT DENSITY WAVES IN THE RINGS.
